  <datafield tag="545" ind1="1" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">President Mary Sue Coleman established the Diversity Blueprints Task Force on December 13, 2006, after Michigan voters approved Proposal 2, a ballot initiative that banned the use of affirmative action or preferential treatment based on race or gender in admissions decisions. Co-chaired by Provost Teresa Sullivan and Senior Vice Provost for Academic Affairs Lester Monts, the Task Force consisted of 55 faculty, students, staff, and administrators and was comprised of four subcommittees related to undergraduate admissions and financial aid, graduate student recruitment and retention, faculty and staff hiring and retention, and educational outreach and engagement. The Task Force released a final report on March 15, 2007 with recommendations for the University to promote and enhance its diversity in light of the new legal requirement.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The materials in this record group document the deliberations and internal as well as external communications of the Diversity Blueprints Task Force and its subcommittees. Administrative files include e-mail, meeting materials, public suggestions, resources, and draft and final versions of the Task Force reports. Archived websites provided a platform to promote the Task Froce's work and disseminate its findings. This series also contains related information on university initiatives to promote diversity.</subfield>
  </datafield>
